text: Daniel Fidelin (born May 25, 1948 in Fécamp) is a member of the National Assembly of France. He represents the Seine-Maritime department, and is a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. ==References== Category:1948 births Category:Living people Category:People from Fécamp Category:Union for a Popular Movement politicians Category:The Popular Right Category:Mayors of places in Normandy Category:Deputies of the 12th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:The Republicans (France) politicians
